subSubSection.paragraph:
BODY. Slender, with parallel margins; the anterior is extremity rounded; the posterior extremity is pointed. The dorsal side is convex; the ventral one is flat; the body margins are rounded. The dorsal color is black and white (
Fig. 10A
). The anterior 10% of the body exhibits a median black band separated from the black margins by a whitish area. Subsequently to this section, a pair of transverse black lines separated by a whitish band appears. From behind these black lines to the posterior end, the color is black except for a median white band (20% of the body width) and large white dots occasionally merged with each other. The ventral side is white, slightly gray in the first two millimeters of the body.
